<HEADLINE> Vote Count From Russian Election  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Vote totals from Sunday's presidential election, with
94.27
percent of the vote counted:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Vladimir Putin: 52.52 percent
</P>
<P>
   Gennady Zyuganov: 29.44 percent
</P>
<P>
   Grigory Yavlinsky: 5.85 percent
</P>
<P>
   Aman Tuleyev: 3.04 percent
</P>
<P>
   Vladimir Zhirinovsky: 2.72 percent
</P>
<P>
   The other six candidates received around 1 percent or less of
the vote each, while 1.9 percent voted against all contenders.
</P>
