effort to attract John McCain supporters and inoculate himself against George W.
Bush's repeated attacks on Gore's past fund-raising abuses. Gore, who said he
was putting campaign reform front-and-center in his Democratic presidential race
after reform proponents McCain and Bill Bradley dropped out, planned to unveil
his plan at a campaign appearance Monday in Milwaukee.
</P>
