<HEADLINE> What They Said at the Oscars  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Quotes from inside and outside the Academy Awards
ceremony
Sunday:
<TEXT>
<P>
   ''I've been told this is the shortest Oscar show of this
century. Good night.'' -- Oscar host Billy Crystal at the end of the
4-hour, 8-minute show.
</P>
<P>
   ''So really, I'm basically up here guys to represent you as what
I hope you will all be and that's a survivor.'' -- Supporting actor
winner Michael Caine.
</P>
<P>
   ''That is the strangest thing that's happened to the suburbs
since the Clintons decided to move to Westchester.'' -- Billy
Crystal after video clips of ''American Beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I would have voted for Warren Beatty for president for one big
reason: Vice President Jack Nicholson.'' -- Billy Crystal.
</P>
<P>
   ''She has given me what I value most, her love, and she's given
me Kathlyn and Ben and Isabel and, at the moment, this much
anticipated and very loved unnamed being who could actually join us
any minute right here in the second row if I don't wrap this up.''
-- Warren Beatty in accepting the Thalberg Award.
</P>
<P>
   ''I first have to say that I would like to dedicate this to the
man who inspired my performance, a man who has been my friend and
my mentor, and since my father died, a little bit like my father,
whose performance in 'The Apartment' stands as one of the finest
we've ever had. Jack Lemmon, wherever you are, thank you, thank
you, thank you.'' -- Kevin Spacey after winning best actor Oscar for
''American Beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   ''His legacy lives on through our movie to remind us to always
be ourselves, to follow our hearts, to not conform. I pray for the
day when we not only accept our differences but we actually
celebrate our diversity.'' -- Oscar winner Hilary Swank on her
''Boys Don't Cry'' character.
</P>
<P>
   ''Well you must be trying to get me to reconsider my day job.''
-- Author John Irving after winning Oscar for screenplay to his
''The Cider House Rules.''
</P>
<P>
   ''It dealt with sex and drugs, blackmail, homophobia, infidelity
and suburbia dysfunction. In the middle of all this was a character
named Ricky Fitts who at one point says, 'Sometimes there's so much
beauty in the world I feel like I can't take it.' And everybody in
the audience knew exactly what he meant.'' -- Dan Jinks, producer of
best movie ''American Beauty.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I just wanted to make sure I got here. That's why I had the
LAPD plant me here.'' -- Billy Crystal after a policeman carried him
onto the stage.
</P>
<P>
   ''I realize you're all alive.'' -- Haley Joel Osment, child star
of ''The Sixth Sense,'' who is known for the key line in the film,
''I see dead people.''
</P>
<P>
   ''We just said a family prayer.'' -- Denzel Washington when asked
what he and his wife did before leaving their four children at home
to attend the Oscars.
</P>
<P>
   ''I haven't worked since I won the Academy Award. I haven't had
anything really good to do. I mean, I got a lot of nasty old men
parts, but that doesn't seem to pay the bills.'' -- James Coburn,
who won an Oscar for his role last year in ''Affliction.''
</P>
</TEXT>
