<HEADLINE> Dow Down 52.52; Nasdaq Up 13.16  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned mostly lower today as Microsoft
fell in advance of a judge's antitrust ruling, weighing on every
major market index.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 52.52 at 11,060.20, having reversed an
early gain.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Nasdaq composite index
was up 13.16 at 4,976.19 and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was
down 3.96 at 1,523.50.
</P>
