<HEADLINE> Moore Leads Tributes for 'Q'  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Former James Bond star Roger Moore led the
tributes Monday at a memorial service for Desmond Llewelyn, who
played the gadget-master Q in several Bond films.
</P>
<P>
   Moore said Llewelyn, who died in a car crash in December at 85,
was a ''wonderful man'' without whom no Bond film would have been
complete. Llewelyn appeared in 17 Bond movies.
</P>
<P>
   The four other men who have played Agent 007 -- Sean Connery,
George Lazenby, Timothy Dalton and Pierce Brosnon -- did not attend
the service.
</P>
