<HEADLINE> Billy Joel Speaks To Boat Builders  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWPORT, R.I. (AP) -- Piano man Billy Joel was in Newport over
the weekend to oversee his latest production: a 14-foot sailboat.
</P>
<P>
   Joel spoke Sunday with students from the Newport Area Career and
Technical Center who are building the boat for him and his
daughter.
</P>
<P>
   The singer saw an old Whitehall in dry dock during a visit to
the seaside town last summer and wondered how he could get one. A
harbormaster put him in contact with the students, who began the
project in October.
</P>
<P>
   Joel made a $10,000 donation to the marine trades program in
exchange for the custom-made vessel.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've always been fascinated with the history of this area, the
different trades that are still here,'' Joel said. ''My daughter
and I and my friends are going to have a lot of fun with this
boat.''
</P>
</TEXT>
