<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Airways Offers Discounts  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Now that it has labor peace, US Airways
moved Monday to try and win back customers scared off by the
prospect of a strike.
</P>
<P>
   The Arlington-based arline announced what it calls ''special
discount sale fares'' for travel in the U.S., Canada, Europe and
the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
   Among the discounted fares being offered are a $258 round trip
between Baltimore and San Francisco, and a $159 round trip from
Washington, D.C. to Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   Travel dates vary by ticket type, but all tickets have to be
purchased at least seven days before departing
</P>
<P>
   US Airways also announced it will award double frequent-flier
miles on all flights through May 15.
</P>
<P>
   The carrier and its 10,000 unionized flight attendants reached a
contract agreement Saturday. The union had been threatening a
series of surprise strikes, which prompted US Airways to threaten
to ground all of its planes.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of US Airways rose 10 percent Monday -- the first trading
day after the settlement -- increasing $2.25 to $24.62{ in trading
on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
