<HEADLINE> Orioles Add Worrell to 40-man Roster  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles purchased the
minor-league contract of reliever Tim Worrell on Monday, adding the
right-hander to their 40-man roster.
</P>
<P>
   Worrell, 32, was signed to a minor league deal Feb. 4 and
invited to the Orioles' major league training camp. His addition
puts the Orioles' roster at the 40-player limit.
</P>
<P>
   In eight relief appearances through Sunday, Worrell went 2-1
with a 1.13 ERA. He has allowed 13 hits over 13 innings with two
walks and eight strikeouts.
</P>
<P>
   In seven major league seasons, Worrell is 20-32 with a 4.46 ERA.
</P>
