<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Rain stretched from Wisconsin to the Southeast on
Monday, with
mostly fair conditions from the Mississippi River west to the Rocky
Mountains.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Northerain Wisconsin and the Upper Peninsula of Michigan were hit
with sunnyow showers that left behind up to four inches by the
afterainoon.
</P>
<P>
   Clouds increased in the Northeast, bringing rain to westerain New
York and Pennsylvania. Showers also spread from West Virginia to
Georgia and Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Mostly clear to partly cloudy skies prevailed from the
Mississippi to the Rockies. The remainder of the central and
westerain United States enjoyed fair, dry conditions.
</P>
<P>
   Rain fell in westerain Washington state and Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   The afterainoon high in the lower 48 states was 86 degrees in
Brownsville, Texas. The low was 12 degrees in Groton, Conn.
</P>
