<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-27 18:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clippers Waive Hudson, Sign Bohannon  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Point guard Troy Hudson, who started 38 games
for the Los Angeles Clippers, was placed on waivers Monday.
</P>
<P>
   To replace Hudson, the Clippers signed 6-foot-9 forward Etdrick
Bohannon to a 10-day contract.
</P>
<P>
   The 24-year-old Hudson averaged 8.8 points and 3.9 assists in 62
games. He played in 25 games for the Clippers last season,
averaging 6.8 points and 3.7 assists.
</P>
<P>
   Bohannon, 26, signed two 10-day contracts with the New York
Knicks earlier this season. He averaged 12.5 points and 10.7
rebounds in 39 games for the Fort Wayne Fury of the Continental
Basketball Association.
</P>
</TEXT>
