<HEADLINE> 'Brockovich' Takes Top Spot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ''Erin Brockovich'' nosed out the new release
''Romeo Must Die'' to lay claim to the top box office spot for the
second weekend in a row.
</P>
<P>
   The legal drama starring Julia Roberts grossed $18.5 million for
the weekend, compared with just over $18 million for the action
film ''Romeo Must Die.''
</P>
<P>
   The teen horror movie ''Final Destination'' was third in its
second week of release, bringing in $7.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   The big winner at the Academy Awards, ''American Beauty,''
picked up a 27 percent bounce over the previous weekend as
moviegoers rushed to see it before Sunday's show. ''The Cider House
Rules'' also saw a pre-Oscar bump in ticket sales.
</P>
