<HEADLINE> Officer Charged With Sexual Assault  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- A police officer was arrested Monday on
charges that he sexually assaulted a man he stopped while on patrol
last year.
</P>
<P>
   Rafael Nieves-Concepcion, 27, was suspended from the force after
surrendering and being charged with sexual assault and other
counts. His attorney said he will plead innocent.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors said Nieves-Concepcion stopped a New York man in his
20s in downtown Philadelphia late on July 1, made the man place his
hands on the officer's patrol car and assaulted him.
</P>
