<HEADLINE> Tar Heels Players Face Court Date  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- North Carolina basketball players Ed
Cota and Terrence Newby are scheduled to appear in court Monday --
the same day the Tar Heels could be playing for a national title in
Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
   Cota and Newby face assault charges in District Court stemming
from a Halloween night brawl. Their trial has been delayed three
times.
</P>
<P>
   That could pose a problem if the Tar Heels beat Florida on
Saturday. That means they would play the Wisconsin-Michigan State
winner in Monday night's championship game.
</P>
<P>
   ''Hopefully, they will excuse them,'' coach Bill Guthridge said.
</P>
