<HEADLINE> Predators' Turcotte Retires  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Nashville Predators center Darren
Turcotte retired Monday, ending his 12-year NHL career.
</P>
<P>
   Turcotte, 32, had 195 goals and 216 assists in 635 games with
the New York Rangers, Hartford, Winnipeg, San Jose, St. Louis and
Nashville. He had a career-high 32 goals for New York in 1989-90,
and represented the Rangers in the 1991 NHL All-Star game.
</P>
<P>
   Turcotte played only nine games this season.
</P>
</TEXT>
