<HEADLINE> Devil Rays' Mecir Injured Warming Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay relief pitcher Jim Mecir is day to
day with a biceps strain, which occurred as he was set to enter
Monday night's game between the Devil Rays and the New York
Yankees.
</P>
<P>
   With two outs in the bottom of the sixth inning, Mecir departed
after one warmup pitch.
</P>
<P>
   ''He felt something in the bicep,'' Tampa Bay manager Larry
Rothschild said. ''It's not his elbow or shoulder, that's the good
news. But again, the bad news is he felt something. Well just
see.''
</P>
<P>
   Mecir is 1-1 with 2.25 ERA in seven games this spring. He
allowed two runs and six hits in eight innings.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know what happened ... it just feels tight,'' Mecir
said. ''It's just a muscle pull. That's all it is.''
</P>
<P>
   Mecir missed most of last season after fracturing his right
elbow during batting practice on May 12. He underwent surgery the
following day by Dr. James Andrews in Birmingham Ala.
</P>
