<HEADLINE> Florida-Based Co. Recalls Antacid  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- The Eckerd Corp. drug store chain is
recalling store-brand antacid tablets from all stores nationwide
after an Arlington woman reported finding a small blade imbedded in
a pill.
</P>
<P>
   ''It looks like a small piece of razor or an Exacto knife,''
Janette Hinkle told Dallas-Fort Worth television station KTVT.
''It's metal, very thin and very sharp.''
</P>
<P>
   The Clearwater, Fla.-based chain is investigating how the blade
got into a package bought Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''The safety and good health of our customers is our primary
concern,'' company officials said in a statement Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Pending our complete and thorough review of this matter, our
quality assurance team will diligently investigate both internally
and with the manufacturer.''
</P>
<P>
   The recall affects antacid pills in 150-tablet bottles with lot
number 1584-680.
</P>
</TEXT>
