<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spurs 90, Sonics 82  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE (AP) -- Tim Duncan scored 30 points and David Robinson
added 23 points as the San Antonio Spurs used a 17-3 fourth quarter
run to beat the Seattle SuperSonics 90-82 on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs twin towers dominated inside with Duncan grabbing 18
rebounds and Robinson 16 to go along with four blocked shots.
</P>
<P>
   The Sonics led 75-71 when the Spurs held Seattle to three
baskets over the final eight minutes. The Sonics lost their fourth
straight home game and slipped into eighth place in the Western
Conference playoff race.
</P>
<P>
   Sean Elliott, playing his seventh game since being activated
after a kidney transplant, scored 10 points, including a key
3-pointer for an 80-76 lead with 5:30 left.
</P>
<P>
   Gary Payton and Vin Baker led the Sonics with 21 points apiece.
Baker appeared to aggravate his left hamstring injury when he fell
with 2:30 left in the game. He did not return.
</P>
<P>
   For the third time in their last four games, the Sonics led in
the fourth quarter but could not hang on.
</P>
<P>
   The Spurs went on an 11-1 run for an 82-76 advantage. Duncan had
four points, Antonio Daniels four and Elliott hit a 3-pointer.
</P>
<P>
   Seattle led 69-68 when Baker scored on an offensive rebound and
Samaki Walker was assessed a technical foul for shoving Jelani
McCoy. Payton's free throw gave Seattle a 72-68 lead with 8:45
left.
</P>
<P>
   Like the other three meetings between the teams, it was close
most of the game. The series is tied at two wins apiece.
</P>
<P>
   Payton scored nine points in the third quarter as the Sonics
were up 66-61 after three periods.
</P>
<P>
   The Sonics opened the third quarter with a 7-0 run on Greg
Foster's basket, a 3-point shot by Brent Barry and Baker's putback
basket for 51-42 advantage with 10:24 left in the quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Foster replaced the injured Grant and gave the Sonics a lift in
the first half with eight points, six rebounds and three assists.
</P>
<P>
   Payton's runner with 3.1 seconds in the half gave the Sonics a
44-42 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Horace Grant did not dress because of a contusion to the
left shoulder during practice Monday. ... Ruben Patterson started
and played the first six minutes but saw limited minutes because of
his sore Achilles tendons. ... Elliott played a season high in
minutes -- 26 -- as he continued his comeback after kidney surgery on
August 16.
</P>
</TEXT>
