<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-27 23:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mavericks 113, Jazz 105  </HEADLINE>
By TIM KORTE, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Michael Finley and the Dallas Mavericks
finally found a way to beat the Utah Jazz.
</P>
<P>
   Finley scored 24 of his 31 points in the first half, Hubert
Davis had 13 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter and Steve Nash
hit six free throws in the final 49.2 seconds as the Dallas
Mavericks beat the Jazz 113-105 on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks snapped a 12-game losing streak to Utah. They
hadn't won in Salt Lake City since Feb. 9, 1989, a span of 25
games. It also was Dallas' first victory in 21 games at the Delta
Center, which opened in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas shot well all night, building a 55-48 halftime lead on
the strength of 55.8 percent shooting.
</P>
<P>
   The loss ended Utah's four-game winning streak, a stretch where
the Jazz had seized control in the fourth quarter. But this time it
was Davis who took over at the end, hitting baskets to thwart every
Utah challenge.
</P>
<P>
   When it was finally over, the Mavericks raised their hands in
celebration and shared handshakes and hugs on the court with new
owner Mark Cuban.
</P>
<P>
   Dirk Nowitzki had 16 points and 17 rebounds, and Erick
Strickland scored 15 for Dallas, which shot 58 percent (40-of-69).
Finley hit 13-of-18.
</P>
<P>
   Karl Malone had 26 points and 10 rebounds to lead Utah but the
Jazz couldn't maintain the momentum that had delivered victories in
13 of their previous 14 games. In fact, Utah looked tired, hitting
48.1 percent (38-of-79).
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks were 10-for-10 from the foul line in the final
minute, with Nash hitting all six of his attempts.
</P>
<P>
   And each time the Jazz made a run in the closing minutes, Davis
delivered. When Utah cut it to 100-93 with 5:58 to play, Davis hit
a jumper. When the Jazz made it 102-95 with 3:01 to go, Davis hit a
3-pointer.
</P>
<P>
   And when Davis missed a 3-point attempt with 1:35, Nowitzki went
out on the perimeter to grab his 17th rebound. He also finished
with eight assists.
</P>
<P>
   During the last three games, the Jazz have been a fourth-quarter
team. They outscored the opposition 89-50 in the final period of
victories over Vancouver, Seattle and Denver.
</P>
<P>
   So the Jazz seemingly had nothing to worry about when Dallas led
88-76 after the third period. And after baskets by Howard Eisley
and Malone cut the deficit to 88-80, Utah seemed poised for a
surge.
</P>
<P>
   But Shawn Bradley scored twice as the Mavericks regained
control, 94-80, with 9:03 to play. And every time the Jazz made a
run after that, Davis hit from the floor or Nash connected from the
line.
</P>
<P>
   Bryon Russell scored 20 for Utah, John Stockton had 16 points
and 14 assists, and Jeff Hornacek scored 14.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Several Jazz players have worked through the flu bug. Greg
Ostertag was listed as doubtful, but started the second quarter.
Hornacek played sick Friday in Seattle, and Malone was ill Saturday
in Vancouver. ... Finley has played in 367 straight games, the
league's second-longest streak. Eisley is next at 348. A.C. Green
of the Lakers has played in 1,098 straight. ... Hornacek, the
league's leading free-throw shooter, missed from the line in the
second quarter. He went 2-of-3 for the game, putting him at
158-of-166 on the season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-27-00 2349 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
